<p>
<h1>Create an API pattern</h1> 
</p>

<p><b>API Platform Base Path:</b> <code>https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1/o/{org_name}</code></p>

<div class="row">
	<div class="span6" style="width:340px;">

		<p><b>API Resource Path:</b> <code>/environment/{env_name}/apipatterns</code></p>
		<p><b>Description:</b> Creates a collection of API patterns, for which operation and business metrics will be collected.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="span6" style="width:340px;">
<table>		
	<tbody><tr><td><b>Verb:</b></td> <td><span class="verb-POST">POST</span></td></tr>
	<tr><td><b>Auth:</b></td> <td>Basic Auth</td></tr>


		<tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><b>Media types:</b></td>  <td>
<div class="content_type" id="content_type_1">
application/json
</div></td></tr>

		</tbody>
</table>


	</div>
</div>

<div class="span18">
	
		
		
	<p><b>Overview: </b>
	</p>
	

	<b>Sample Request:</b>
	<div class="terminal">$ curl -H "Content-type:application/json" -X POST -d \ 
'{“apipatterns” : [
{
            "apiproxy": "StoreLocator",
            "request_verb": "GET",
            "apipattern": "/v1/books/*/stores/*"
        },
{
            "apiproxy": "StoreLocator",
            "request_verb": "POST”,
            "apipattern": "/v1/books/*/stores/*"
        },
{
            "apiproxy": "StoreLocator",
            "request_verb": "GET",
            "apipattern": "/v1/stores/*/cities"
        }
] }' \
https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1/o/{org_name}/environments/{env_name}/apipatterns \
-u myname:mypass</div>
	<b>Request Payload Elements:</b> 
	<table class="table table-bordered">
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Name</th>
				<th>Description</th>
				<th>Default</th>
				<th>Required?</th>
			</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
<div class="request_element" id="request_element_94">
<td>apipatterns</td>
<td>The base element of a collection of apipatterns</td>
<td>N/A</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<!-- <td><a href="/request_elements/94" class="btn btn-mini">Detail</a></td> -->
</div></tr>


<tr>
<div class="request_element" id="request_element_95">
<td>apiproxy</td>
<td>The name of an API proxy in the environment, to which metrics will be scoped by the pattern</td>
<td>N/A</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<!-- <td><a href="/request_elements/95" class="btn btn-mini">Detail</a></td> -->
</div></tr>


<tr>
<div class="request_element" id="request_element_96">
<td>request_verb</td>
<td> The HTTP associated with request messages, to which metrics will be scoped by the pattern</td>
<td>N/A</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<!-- <td><a href="/request_elements/96" class="btn btn-mini">Detail</a></td> -->
</div></tr>


<tr>
<div class="request_element" id="request_element_97">
<td>apipattern</td>
<td> The URI path pattern associated with request messages, to which metrics will be scoped by the pattern</td>
<td>N/A</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<!-- <td><a href="/request_elements/97" class="btn btn-mini">Detail</a></td> -->
</div></tr>



			</table>


<b>Sample Response:</b> 
	<pre>{“apipatterns” : [
{
            "apiproxy": "StoreLocator",
            "request_verb": "GET",
            "apipattern": "/v1/books/*/stores/*",
            "groupid": "1"
        },
{
            "apiproxy": "StoreLocator",
            "request_verb": "POST”,
            "apipattern": "/v1/books/*/stores/*",
            "groupid": "2"
        },
{
            "apiproxy": "StoreLocator",
            "request_verb": "GET",
            "apipattern": "/v1/stores/*/cities",
            "groupid": "3"
        }
]}</pre>

	<b>Response Payload Elements:</b>
		<table class="table table-bordered">
			<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Name</th>
				<th>Description</th>
			</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
<div class="response_element" id="response_element_715">
<td>apiproxy </td>
<td>The name of an API proxy in the environment</td>
</div></tr><tr>
<div class="response_element" id="response_element_716">
<td>request_verb </td>
<td>The HTTP verb associated with request messages</td>
</div></tr><tr>
<div class="response_element" id="response_element_717">
<td>apipattern </td>
<td>The URI matching pattern used to collect metrics for this API patternn</td>
</div></tr><tr>
<div class="response_element" id="response_element_718">
<td>groupid </td>
<td>System-generated unique number that identifies the API pattern</td>
</div></tr>
		</table>

	
